  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(inductive)::set]\nRefines: A\nsatisfies:\n. \\set.theoretic.zero \"in\" A\n. forAll: x is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\n  where: x \"in\" A\n  then: \\set.theoretic.successor{x} \"in\" A\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"inductive\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{inductive}\"\n. description: \"A set $A$ is inductive, or a successor set, when $0 \\in A$ and $x \\in A$ implies $x^+ \\in A$. Inductive sets are the sets closed under the successor operation and containing zero.\"\nId: \"92407cb2-fc01-41a2-a223-3b2671145f65\"",
